.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
The \fBSoVRMLCoordinate\fP class is used to define 3D coordinates for shapes\&.
.PP
\fBThe detailed class documentation is taken verbatim from the VRML97 standard (ISO/IEC 14772-1:1997)\&. It is copyright The Web3D Consortium, and is used by permission of the Consortium:\fP 


.PP
.nf
Coordinate { 
  exposedField MFVec3f point  []      # (-inf, inf) 
}

.fi
.PP
.PP
This node defines a set of 3D coordinates to be used in the coord field of vertex-based geometry nodes including \fBSoVRMLIndexedFaceSet\fP, \fBSoVRMLIndexedLineSet\fP, and \fBSoVRMLPointSet\fP\&. 
